Attribution for upstream and reference projects
================================================================================

htmlwasher is a TypeScript port of Trafilatura. It is derived from,
informed by, and references the projects listed below. Their authors are
credited here as required by their respective licenses. The text of the
Apache License, Version 2.0 referenced below is reproduced in this repository's
LICENSE file.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Trafilatura (the canonical original) — Apache-2.0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:  Adrien Barbaresi
Source:  https://github.com/adbar/trafilatura
Docs:    https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/

The canonical original. htmlwasher follows its extraction semantics,
metadata rules, option behavior, and test corpus as the ground-truth reference.

Citation:
  Barbaresi, A. (2021). "Trafilatura: A Web Scraping Library and Command-Line
  Tool for Text Discovery and Extraction." Proceedings of the Joint Conference
  of the 59th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics
  and the 11th International Joint Conference on Natural Language Processing:
